<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('./partials/head') -%>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>URL Shortener API</h1>
      <h2>Created by <a href="https://autumnbullard-portfolio.herokuapp.com" target="_blank">Autumn Bullard</a> &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear(); %></h2>
      <p>My project for the <a href="https://learn.freecodecamp.org/apis-and-microservices/apis-and-microservices-projects/url-shortener-microservice" target="_blank">URL Shortener Microservice challenge</a> as part of the curriculum for the Apis and Microservices Certification on <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org" target="_blank">freeCodeCamp</a>.</p>
      <p>View the <a href="https://github.com/autumnchris/url-shortener-api" target="_blank">source code</a> for this project.</p>
      <hr>
    </header>
    <main>
      <h3>Project Usage</h3>
      <p>Submit a web address in the form below to get a generated alias that will be used to redirect to the original URL.</p>
      <p>For example, if I wanted an alias URL that will redirect to GitHub's homepage I would paste <code>https://github.com</code>in the input field and upon submission I would receive a new URL as my alias that I can then use to redirect to the original URL that I submitted.</p>
      <form action="/api/shorturl/new" method="post">
        <div class="form-group">
          <input type="text" name="url" placeholder="Paste a URL to be shortened" aria-label="Paste a URL to be shortened" required>
        </div>
        <div class="button-group">
          <input type="submit" value="Submit">
        </div>
      </form>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
